    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Mythical animals with a single horn, sometimes identified as a type of unicorn. In legend, the appearance of the qilin coincided with the birth or death of a great ruler or sage, such as Confucius. Representations of qilin often appear on a spirit way, lining the path to a tomb.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
